ChromeOS is an operating system used and developed almost exclusively by Google in order to used on the Chromebook hardware line. ChromeOS is built<ref>http://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/packages</ref> using [[Portage]]<ref>http://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/packages/portage</ref>, Gentoo's package manager, and Gentoo-based [[chroot]]s<ref>http://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/build/sdk-creation#TOC-Introduction</ref>.

